# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: PrisonArc | Scene: OutsideAndAlone3
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah look off to the side of the alley and waves for attention."
    new "Sarah look off to the side of the alley and waves for attention."

    old "Instinctively, the brigand's eyes follow where she is looking at."
    new "Instinctively, the brigand's eyes follow where she is looking at."

    old "But only a moment too late, he realizes there isn't anyone there."
    new "But only a moment too late, he realizes there isn't anyone there."

    old "He's a moment too slow and a moment too late, and by the time he turns back, the girl has slipped under his arm."
    new "He's a moment too slow and a moment too late, and by the time he turns back, the girl has slipped under his arm."

    old "Sarah drives her elbow into the man's rib cage, causing him to slip and fall back."
    new "Sarah drives her elbow into the man's rib cage, causing him to slip and fall back."

    old "You bitch! Get back here!"
    new "You bitch! Get back here!"

    old "Sarah never stops to turn around, in a mad dash, she's out of the alley and onto the street."
    new "Sarah never stops to turn around, in a mad dash, she's out of the alley and onto the street."

    old "She keeps running, running for the docks where she knows there will be people, even at this hour."
    new "She keeps running, running for the docks where she knows there will be people, even at this hour."

    old "She thinks she can hear him running after her, but in time, the footsteps fade."
    new "She thinks she can hear him running after her, but in time, the footsteps fade."

    old "Only when she gets back to the harbor district does she finally turn around."
    new "Only when she gets back to the harbor district does she finally turn around."

    old "Nobody is following her anymore. She's safe."
    new "Nobody is following her anymore. She's safe."

    old "Sarah collapses onto one of the benches. Off into the distance, she can see the first rays of sunlight creeping over the horizon."
    new "Sarah collapses onto one of the benches. Off into the distance, she can see the first rays of sunlight creeping over the horizon."

    old "One day."
    new "One day."

    old "She survived one day in Lethram."
    new "She survived one day in Lethram."

    old "Sarah pushes herself upright, leaning her back against the bench's backrest."
    new "Sarah pushes herself upright, leaning her back against the bench's backrest."

    old "Around her she can see the early signs of the harbor waking up. Barely sober sailors stumbling towards the docked ships. Carts drawn by longshoremen, loading and unloading the cargo."
    new "Around her she can see the early signs of the harbor waking up. Barely sober sailors stumbling towards the docked ships. Carts drawn by longshoremen, loading and unloading the cargo."

    old "Sarah tried to let the early morning sun wake her up."
    new "Sarah tried to let the early morning sun wake her up."

    old "She had been out on her own in this city for a single day and she had nearly been attacked."
    new "She had been out on her own in this city for a single day and she had nearly been attacked."

    old "Flashes of the night before came back to her, the dangerous looking man with his dagger, his ravenous eyes..."
    new "Flashes of the night before came back to her, the dangerous looking man with his dagger, his ravenous eyes..."

    old "Never in her life had she met such a dangerous man before."
    new "Never in her life had she met such a dangerous man before."

    old "Sarah calmed herself, preventing her mind from racing. No use thinking of what might have happened. She had managed to get away."
    new "Sarah calmed herself, preventing her mind from racing. No use thinking of what might have happened. She had managed to get away."

    old "But would she be so lucky next time, Sarah wasn't so sure."
    new "But would she be so lucky next time, Sarah wasn't so sure."

    old "Lethram was an unkind place to most, but it was certainly unkind to women who had no money or other means to protect themselves."
    new "Lethram was an unkind place to most, but it was certainly unkind to women who had no money or other means to protect themselves."

    old "And yet, Sarah's life had not prepared her for this. She had no idea how to make money."
    new "And yet, Sarah's life had not prepared her for this. She had no idea how to make money."

    old "Tears began to swell in her eyes."
    new "Tears began to swell in her eyes."

    old "Sarah nearly yelled the word, commanding herself to stay in control."
    new "Sarah nearly yelled the word, commanding herself to stay in control."

    old "Don't cry. Your life is in the balance, one mistake and who knew what would happen. That vile criminal could find her, or who knew what worse this city had in store."
    new "Don't cry. Your life is in the balance, one mistake and who knew what would happen. That vile criminal could find her, or who knew what worse this city had in store."

    old "Sarah stood up and scanned her suroundings. It was time to make a decision."
    new "Sarah stood up and scanned her suroundings. It was time to make a decision."

    old "Explore the city"
    new "Explore the city"

    old "Sarah didn't yet know what she had to do."
    new "Sarah didn't yet know what she had to do."

    old "But she also knew that she wasn't going to find the answer by sitting around here."
    new "But she also knew that she wasn't going to find the answer by sitting around here."

    old "Surely, somewhere in this cursed city, there would be a single kind hearted person that might take her in."
    new "Surely, somewhere in this cursed city, there would be a single kind hearted person that might take her in."

    old "Having made up her mind, Sarah stood up and began to walk away from the harbor district."
    new "Having made up her mind, Sarah stood up and began to walk away from the harbor district."

    old "Explore the docks"
    new "Explore the docks"

    old "She'd run back to the docks, the first place she'd ever seen when she arrived in Lethram."
    new "She'd run back to the docks, the first place she'd ever seen when she arrived in Lethram."

    old "This was the heart of the city, the center of its economy. Ships arrived and departed to every corner of the world."
    new "This was the heart of the city, the center of its economy. Ships arrived and departed to every corner of the world."

    old "Somewhere in the harbor district, there had to be someone that could help her."
    new "Somewhere in the harbor district, there had to be someone that could help her."

    old "Leave Lethram"
    new "Leave Lethram"

    old "She wasn't safe anywhere in this forsaken city. She would have to leave."
    new "She wasn't safe anywhere in this forsaken city. She would have to leave."

    old "She was close to the main road that ran through Lethram center. From there, the road ran all the way up the hills where the city gates opened out to the hinterlands."
    new "She was close to the main road that ran through Lethram center. From there, the road ran all the way up the hills where the city gates opened out to the hinterlands."

    old "From there, a long stretch of small farming communities. Good people, the kinds of communities that had no crime."
    new "From there, a long stretch of small farming communities. Good people, the kinds of communities that had no crime."

